# Actuary (Aktuari)

## Definition
Uses mathematics and statistics to help companies predict financial risk and future expenses. Heavy Excel use; some coding. Works within insurance, consulting, and related financial services.

## Industry
Banking & Finance

## Salary Range
- Starting: RM 2,800–7,000
- Leadership (Appointed Actuary): RM 30,000–75,000+

## Career Levels
Early Career → Supervisory (~2 yrs) → Managerial (~6 yrs) → Leadership (~15 yrs)

## Education Pathways
- **Degree route (4–6 yrs):** Actuarial Science degree → Actuarial Associate
- **Professional certification route (7–13 yrs):** Any degree + IFoA/SOA exams → Certified Actuary
- Non-Actuarial Science degree holders can enter via professional exams (may sit more exams without exemptions)

## Aliases on Schola
Valuation Actuary · Actuarial Executive · Mathematician · Demographer

## Demand
High demand in Malaysian insurance companies, consulting firms, and internationally — demand grows with certification and experience.

